Redis Client Example with Node.js

📌 Overview

This project demonstrates how to connect to a Redis server using Node.js. It covers basic Redis operations like setting/getting values, working with hashes, lists, sets, and using the publish/subscribe feature for real-time messaging.

🛠 Installation & Setup

1️⃣ Prerequisites

Node.js (Ensure you have Node.js installed)

Redis (Install and run Redis on your system)

Install Redis on Linux (Ubuntu/Debian)

sudo apt update
sudo apt install redis

Install Redis on macOS (Using Homebrew)

brew install redis

Install Redis on Windows

Use WSL (Windows Subsystem for Linux) or install via Memurai for Windows.

2️⃣ Start Redis Server

Before running the Node.js script, ensure Redis is running.

redis-server

Verify Redis is running by checking:

redis-cli ping
# Response: PONG

3️⃣ Install Node.js Dependencies

Navigate to the project folder and install Redis client for Node.js: